content: Hello all, I ran the bisect tool for an ICE (issue #92537), and the result is that there was a regression in a commit that seems completely off-topic (https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/commit/50171c310cd15e1b2d3723766ce64e2e4d6696fc)
NVM that commit is actually when Cargo switched from 2018 to 2021
Patrick Poitras has marked this topic as resolved.
The reason it was no longer giving me an ICE is because it just crashed at "edition" = "2021". :sweat_smile:
Yeah, the bisection can sometimes give you weird results like that if an unrelated error occurs
